#Import data set

nba <- read.csv("NBAdraft.csv", check.names = F)


#remove rank 
nba <- subset(nba, select = -c(1))
#head(nba)
#str(nba)

#remove school, name and lottery column 
nba <- subset(nba, select=-c(2,28,29))

nba$Pk <- as.numeric(nba$Pk)
nba$G_college <- as.numeric(nba$G_college)
nba$GS <- as.numeric(nba$GS)
#str(nba)
cbind(
   lapply(
     lapply(nba, is.na)
     , sum)
   )

#3P%_college has NAs so remove column ###drop rows instead 
#do poly for all variables and linear, drop spline 
nba <- nba[!is.na(nba$`3P%_college`), ]

#Split into train/test

set.seed(1128)
train_index <- createDataPartition(nba$Pk, p=0.8,
                                   list=FALSE,
                                   times=1)
nba_train <- nba[train_index, ]
nba_test <- nba[-train_index, ]

#Linear Regression all Variables

lm_nba = lm(Pk ~., data=nba_train)
#summary(lm_nba)
#

#set up CV and control parameters 
metric <- "RMSE"
tuneLength <- 10

linearModelReg_total <- caret::train(Pk ~ G_college+GS+MP_college+FG+FGA+`FG%_college`+`2P`+`2PA`+`2P%`+`3P`+`3PA`+`3P%_college`+FT+FTA+`FT%_college`+ORB+DRB+TRB_college+AST_college+STL+BLK+TOV+PF+PTS_college+SOS, data=nba_train, metric=metric, preProc = c("center", "scale"), method="lm", tuneLength=tuneLength)

summary(linearModelReg_total)

#Polynomial

poly_reg <- lm(Pk ~ poly(G_college,2)+poly(GS,2)+ poly(MP_college,2)+poly(FG,2)+poly(FGA,2)+poly(`FT%_college`,2) + +poly(`2P`,2)+poly(`2PA`,2)+poly(`2P%`,2)+poly(`3P`,2)+poly(`3PA`,2)+poly(`3P%_college`,2)+poly(FT,2) + poly(FTA, 2)+poly(`FT%_college`,2)+poly(ORB,2)+poly(DRB,2)+poly(TRB_college,2)+poly(AST_college,2) + poly(STL,2)+poly(BLK,2)+poly(TOV,2)+poly(PF,2)+poly(PTS_college,2) + poly(SOS,2), data=nba_train)


#stargazer::stargazer(poly_reg, type='text', summary=TRUE,report = "vc*stp",ci=TRUE)

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(poly_reg, col="blue", pch=21)

predictionpoly1 <-predict(poly_reg,newdata = nba_test)
# 
rmsepoly<-RMSE(predictions, nba_test$Pk)
# 
error.rate.poly <- rmse/mean(nba_test$Pk)
